# ResumeForge

## Layout

- Resume canvas is **A4** using `A4_WIDTH_PX` / `A4_HEIGHT_PX` from [src/constants/layout.ts](src/constants/layout.ts). Keep [pdf-service/server.mjs](pdf-service/server.mjs) viewport and `page.pdf` dimensions in sync when changing these.

## Templates

- Add templates in [src/templates/registry.ts](src/templates/registry.ts): metadata in `templates` array **and** an entry in `templateComponents` with matching `id`.
- Implement the UI in `src/templates/...` (see existing `modern/`, `additional/SetA.tsx`, etc.). Template components use `useResume()`; they must render a root at **794×1123** px (or use shared constants).
- **Do not** hand-build separate mini-previews on the templates gallery — use [TemplateThumbnail](src/components/TemplateThumbnail.tsx) (real `ResumePreview` + `sampleResume`).
- Prefer `category`, `bestFor`, and `colors` on the `Template` type for gallery cards.

## PDF

- PDF export requires **`VITE_PDF_SERVICE_URL`** (see [.env.example](.env.example)); no API URL is hardcoded in the app. `resolvePdfExportUrl()` in [EditorPage](src/pages/EditorPage.tsx) accepts a full `.../pdf` URL or a base URL (appends `/pdf` when missing). The Playwright server lives in [pdf-service](pdf-service/). Ensure **CORS** on the PDF server allows your static site origin.
- PDF matches the **same React templates** as the live preview; prefer solid `color` for headings (avoid `background-clip: text`) for consistency across browsers.

## Data

- Gallery and tests use [sampleResume](src/data/sampleResume.ts) via `ResumeProvider`’s `initialResumeData` / `initialTemplate`.
